      "summary_en": "U.S. equities softened modestly on April 29 as investors remained cautious ahead of key economic data and ongoing uncertainty around trade policy. The NASDAQ led declines at -0.9%, dragged by weakness in large-cap tech, while the broader S&P 500 fell -0.5% in lighter trading. With no clear catalyst to push markets higher, the session reflected a wait-and-see posture among institutional players.",
